Frank Cochrane https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frank_Cochrane 0 Frank Cochrane (28 October 1882 – 21 May 1962) was a British stage and film actor. Born in Durham, England. Amongst his stage work, he starred in the original production of Chu Chin Chow at His Majesty's Theatre in London in 1916; as well as in the 1934 film version.
